## 3. Key Findings

### 3.1 Revenue Distribution by Category

| Category | Revenue | Revenue Share | Units Sold | Unique Products |
|----------|---------|---------------|------------|-----------------|
| Coffee | $89,432 | 58.3% | 18,234 | 18 |
| Tea | $40,987 | 26.7% | 8,456 | 10 |
| Chocolate | $23,012 | 15.0% | 4,891 | 7 |
| **Total** | **$153,431** | **100%** | **31,581** | **35** |

**Insight:** Coffee is the dominant category with 58.3% revenue share, indicating moderate business dependency. This is healthy as it remains under the 60% risk threshold. Tea shows strong performance as secondary category.

### 3.2 Revenue Concentration (Pareto Analysis)

| Metric | Value | Assessment |
|--------|-------|------------|
| Products generating 80% of revenue | 8 out of 35 (22.9%) | ✅ Healthy |
| Top 20% products revenue contribution | 76.4% | ✅ Efficient |
| Bottom 50% products revenue contribution | 8.7% | ⚠️ Review needed |

**Insight:** The revenue concentration follows a healthy pattern (22.9% is close to the ideal 20%). However, bottom 50% of products (17 products) contribute only 8.7% of revenue, suggesting menu simplification opportunities.

