| 🟡 Medium | Feature top 3 hero products in marketing | +10% revenue from hero products (+$4,400) |
| 🟢 Low | Test seasonal rotation for 6 niche products | Menu freshness, customer interest |

### 5.2 Category-Specific Strategies

**Coffee Category (58.3% revenue - $89,432 - Maintain):**
- Protect supply chain for top 3 coffee products (Caramel Macchiato, Classic Latte, Vanilla Cold Brew)
- Introduce limited-edition seasonal blends quarterly
- Consider premium pricing (+$0.50) for star coffee products
- Remove Decaf Americano (only 1.02% revenue share)

**Tea Category (26.7% revenue - $40,987 - Grow):**
- Expand tea product types based on Earl Grey success
- Create tea pairing recommendations with pastries
- Implement tea loyalty program (buy 10 get 1 free)
- Review Matcha Green Tea (only 0.51% revenue) - reposition or remove

**Chocolate Category (15% revenue - $23,012 - Optimize):**
- Remove White Chocolate Mocha (0.37% revenue)
- Bundle Mocha Delight with coffee as combo deals
- Test premium dark chocolate offerings
- Convert Peppermint Mocha to seasonal winter item

### 5.3 Long-Term Strategic Recommendations (6-12 Months)

1. **Menu Optimization**
   - Quarterly review of bottom 10% products (3-4 products)
   - Maintain SKU count between 25-30 products (reduce from 35)
   - Implement seasonal rotation program for 6 niche products

2. **Pricing Strategy**
   - Dynamic pricing for peak hours (7-9 AM, 12-2 PM)
   - Volume discounts only for star products (buy 5 get 1 free)
   - Premium tier (+$1.00) for limited editions

3. **Product Development**
   - Focus new product development on Coffee category
   - Create hero product variants (Caramel Macchiato with oat milk)
   - Discontinue underperformers before adding new items

